IronWASP v0.9.6.5 Release

* Support for SOAP data format added
* XML, JSON, Multipart and SOAP Format Plugins have been implemented in
C#
* XML, JSON, Multipart and SOAP are now auto-detected in
Request/Response and parsed
* Redesigned RequestView to make parameter more easily accessible
* Added ability to view/edit a single parameter in a multi-line textarea
with hex support
* Major redesign in the Results section
* Request and Response triggers are not automatically highlighted in the
results view
* Request and Response triggers now carry a description field as well
* More meta data about a Finding is now stored
* Trigger Analysis Tools are added. One-click view of the Scan trace
associated with a finding and easy diff of the triggers
* The Baseline Request and Response is now shown in Findings along with
the Triggers
* Scan Trace Viewer now automatically performs Payload Effect Analysis
and shows the results
* Scan Trace Viewer now shows colour highlighting and trace information
in the Logs section
* Scan Trace Viewer now automatically shows diff between selected log
and baseline log
* Payload Effect Analysis summary is made cleaner and more visually
appealing.
* 'Create New Request' feature of Manual Testing now automatically
detects Request from the clipboard and gives option to use that
* No need for the Click Action radio button anymore, selecting an
viewing logs is much easier
* Many more minor updates
* Many bug fixes

Dismiss of dialog with cancel then show immediately causes button to stick around (not any more)

Small bug (thanks José Jorge Ferreira) where if you show a HUD with a cancel button, then dismiss it, then immediately show another one (usually an image), the cancel button will stick around. The button was being removed after the animation finished

Merge pull request #33 from seanlindo/master

Exposing CountryCode
Do not generate undo information when updating SOP properties from DSG module

Prevent OnRemovePresence from sending SyncMsgRemovedPresence when presence has already been removed from sync cache. Every actor was echoing the remove presence message. Could have checked for LocallyGeneratedEvent signature but this is more robust

Prevent OnObjectBeingRemovedFromScene from sending a SyncMsgRemovedObject when the object is not found in the sync cache. This was causing every actor to echo the remove message back to every actor after is processed the delete. Checking LocallyGeneratedEvent signature could have caught this too but this solution is more resilient to other timing issues

Fix race condition and exception where an updated updateProperties
message didn't completely zero out the information from the origional
update.
Optimize SyncMsgRemovedObject:HandleIn for the case where removed prim is the root prim of SOG. This eliminates the need to search the GetGroupByPrim

Remove updates from the outgoing queue when deleting a scene object. Also, all SyncMsg types that are expected to have DataLength=0 now derive from SyncMsg instead of SyncMsgOSDDataMap. When updates are sent and the object has been deleted or the properties cannot be encoded, do not send empty map to other connectors

Merge pull request #3 from mikdav/PlivoXmlFixes

Fixing an issue when adding nested elements

Calling a method to add a nested element returns the parent element, and not the newly nested element.  This makes it impossible to reference the newly created element and makes all of the helper functions (like AddDial) useless because you have to new up a Dial element to have access to it anyway.

Fix is to return the nested element instead of 'this'.

Create README.md

The service consists of a simple self-hosted WebApi controller with a single Index action that returns the current Date and time as a string.

The installer automatically installs and starts the service during installation, and will stop and remove the service during uninstallation. 

It also demonstrates how to use a custom action to enable a WCF namespace reservation on a TCP port during the installation. This solution is thanks to Geoff Webber: 
    http://geoffwebbercross.blogspot.com/2011/08/wix-3-netsh-customaction.html
